claire....what will be the business scenario for that .....when there are 2 diff item returned on two diff dates....
diff return event will there ....which will not be having returnordernum...like in the case of direct walkin which is not web initiated ....
there will no record with returnordernum....so there will be more than one record against odernum...carriercode and statuscode ....which record to consider ....out of 2

The return order number is exclusively used in the filter when the input type is included in Pravin's provided list. Claire, please explain the business scenario in which two different items are returned on two different dates. In this scenario, there will be a different return event that does not have a return order number, such as a direct walk-in that is not initiated through the web. As a result, there will be multiple records against the order number, carrier code, and status code. Which record should be considered out of the two?
